  "prompt": "Is Niacin added in the preparation of cannabis?",
  "response": "Niacin, also known as vitamin B3, is not typically added in the preparation of cannabis. The preparation of cannabis usually involves processes such as drying, curing, trimming, and sometimes decarboxylation, but these steps do not generally include the addition of niacin.\n\nHowever, some anecdotal reports and online forums suggest that certain individuals might use niacin in an attempt to enhance the effects of cannabis or to mask its presence in drug tests. These uses are not supported by scientific evidence and can be potentially harmful.\n\nIf you have specific concerns about cannabis preparation or the use of niacin, it's best to consult with a healthcare professional or a knowledgeable expert in the field.",
